Privacy Policy for CertifyMe Chrome Extension

Effective Date: 12-21-2024

CertifyMe ("we", "our", "us") is a Chrome extension designed to help users discover free and discounted certification programs and track their progress.

Data Collection: CertifyMe does not collect any personally identifiable information or sensitive data from its users. All user data is stored locally in the browser and is used only to track the user's progress in certification courses. No data is transferred to third-party servers.

Storage: The extension uses the browser's local storage to save progress data, which is only accessible by the user.

No Data Sharing: We do not share or sell any user data to third parties. The data stored is for personal use only, to help users keep track of their certifications.

Changes to Privacy Policy: We may update this privacy policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices. We will notify users of any major changes.

Contact: If you have any questions about this privacy policy, please contact us at tchoutezoramses3@gmail.com.
